## Technical Debt Notes

1. **`BranchMigrationRunner.java`** — This startup migration infers branch ownership from sales invoice history and user creation trails. This is a one-time migration artifact and should be removed or made conditional (run-once flag in DB) to avoid re-processing on every startup.

2. **`Branch` stored as `String branch` in legacy sales entities vs `Long branchId`** — The migration runner bridges this gap, but after migration completes, the old `branch: String` column should be deprecated and dropped.

3. **`BranchContext.jsx` resolution chain** — The 3-step fallback (profile → list → API) adds 3 serial API calls on every app load. After branch scoping is stable, this should be collapsed into 1 consolidated endpoint: `GET /api/me/context` that returns user profile + resolved branch in a single call.

---

## Decision Required from You

> **Before any implementation begins, please clarify:**
>
> 1. Is BillBull being sold to **single-location clients** (shops, small retailers) or always to **multi-branch businesses**?
> 2. For single-location clients, do they still need a "Branch Setup" page, or should it be completely hidden?
> 3. Should ADMIN users be able to **create documents on behalf of any branch**, or only view cross-branch reports?

The answers will determine whether we implement the **Business Mode toggle** on the Company page or simply improve the existing Branch Setup page.
